definitions.definition: ( botany , uncountable ) The dead protective tissue between the bark and cambium in woody plants, with suberin deposits making it impervious to gasses and water.

subdefinitions.definition: The phellem of the cork oak , used for making bottle stoppers, flotation devices, and insulation material.

definitions.definition: A bottle stopper made from this or any other material.
examples: Snobs feel it's hard to call it wine with a straight face when the cork is made of plastic.

definitions.definition: An angling float , also traditionally made of oak cork.

definitions.definition: An aerialist maneuver involving a rotation where the rider goes heels over head, with the board overhead.
